readme_summary: User Scanner is a Python-based OSINT tool designed for both email and username analysis across numerous platforms. It helps security researchers and investigators quickly determine the presence of an email or the availability of a username on various social, developer, and creator sites.
key_features: Dual-mode usage (email scanner, username scanner, or username-only)
Modular architecture for easy platform addition
Proxy support with rotation and validation
primary_use_case: Performing OSINT investigations by checking email registrations and username availability across multiple online platforms.
cover_image_prompt: A digital detective, wearing a trench coat and holding a magnifying glass that glows with data streams, stands before a wall of interconnected social media icons. The magnifying glass is focused on a specific email address and a username, revealing glowing 'Registered' or 'Available' status tags floating next to each icon. Subtle code snippets and data visualizations appear as background elements, and the repository name 'User Scanner' is subtly integrated into a digital display on the detective's wrist. The scene is rendered in a 3D isometric illustration style with a dark, mysterious color palette and neon blue accents, emphasizing the digital investigation.

name: Linly-Dubbing
readme_summary: Linly-Dubbing is an intelligent AI-powered tool designed for multi-language video dubbing and translation. It automates video downloading, vocal separation, speech recognition, translation, and AI-driven speech synthesis, enhanced with digital human lip-sync technology for natural and accurate multilingual content.
key_features: Large Language Model Translation (OpenAI API, Qwen, Google Translate)
AI-Powered Speech Synthesis (Edge TTS, XTTS, CosyVoice, GPT-SoVITS)
primary_use_case: To enable seamless and high-quality multi-language dubbing and translation for videos, making content accessible globally.
cover_image_prompt: A vibrant, magical translation booth where a video stream is fed in as raw, jumbled sound waves and text. Inside the booth, a friendly AI robot with glowing circuits meticulously sorts these elements, transforming them into perfectly synchronized, multi-colored sound waves and translated subtitles that flow out to different global audiences represented by diverse, happy faces. Subtle UI elements showing language selection and audio waveforms are visible on the robot's console. The scene is brightly lit with a clean, modern aesthetic, rendered in a 3D isometric illustration style with clear, friendly iconography and a colorful, optimistic palette.

name: openclaw
description: Your own personal AI assistant. Any OS. Any Platform. The lobster way. ü¶û
readme_summary: OpenClaw is a personal AI assistant that runs locally on your devices, integrating with various communication channels like WhatsApp, Telegram, and Slack. It allows users to have a fast, always-on, and private AI experience, supporting multiple LLM providers and offering features like voice interaction and live canvas rendering.
key_features: Personal AI assistant running on user devices
Integration with multiple communication channels (WhatsApp, Telegram, Slack, Discord, Google Chat, Signal, iMessage, Microsoft Teams, WebChat, BlueBubbles, Matrix, Zalo)
Voice and listening capabilities on macOS/iOS/Android
primary_use_case: To provide users with a private, fast, and always-on personal AI assistant that integrates seamlessly with their existing communication platforms.
cover_image_prompt: A friendly, stylized lobster wearing a small headset and sitting at a clean, modern desk. The lobster is actively communicating through multiple glowing holographic chat bubbles representing WhatsApp, Telegram, and Slack, which are floating around it. In front of the lobster, a small, interactive digital canvas displays a simple, evolving illustration. Subtle lines of light connect the lobster to these chat bubbles and the canvas, symbolizing data flow. The overall mood is helpful and efficient, with a clean, bright aesthetic. The style should be a 3D isometric illustration with smooth textures and a focus on clarity and approachability, with the OpenClaw logo subtly integrated into the desk.

name: arozos
description: Web Desktop Operating System for low power platforms, Now written in Go!
readme_summary: ArozOS is a web-based desktop operating system designed for low-power platforms like Raspberry Pi. It provides a user-friendly interface, extensive file and disk management capabilities, networking tools, and security features, all accessible through a web browser.
key_features: File Manager with drag-and-drop and upload support
Static Web Server with built-in editor
Disk mounting for local and remote file systems
Network File Sharing Servers (FTP, WebDAV, SFTP)
File Sharing similar to Google Drive
Support for low system memory (512MB) and storage (1.5GB)
primary_use_case: To provide a functional and accessible desktop operating system experience on low-power devices, primarily for home server, NAS, and cloud storage management, accessible via a web browser.
cover_image_prompt: A miniature, vibrant desktop computer motherboard, like a tiny city, with glowing data streams flowing between its components. A friendly, stylized web browser window hovers above, acting as a portal or a control panel, displaying organized file icons and network graphs. Small, stylized icons representing cloud storage and network drives are connected to the motherboard via digital pathways. The overall aesthetic is clean, modern, and slightly futuristic, emphasizing accessibility and control. The scene should be rendered in a 3D isometric illustration style with a bright, inviting color palette, clearly conveying a powerful yet compact operating system experience for embedded devices.

key_features: Support for structured, semi-structured, and unstructured data
Fully open-source model, code, and training data

name: Asspp
description: The App Store for your multi-account eco system.
readme_summary: Asspp is a Swift-based application that provides a centralized management system for multiple Apple IDs within the App Store ecosystem. It allows users to manage apps across different accounts and regions, facilitating app discovery, download, and installation on non-jailbroken devices, including the ability to manage historical versions.
primary_use_case: Managing multiple Apple IDs and their associated App Store content (apps, historical versions) on a single device, simplifying app acquisition and installation.
cover_image_prompt: A whimsical, stylized 'App Store' building with multiple distinct doors, each labeled with a different Apple ID icon. A friendly, multi-armed librarian character is actively sorting and distributing app icons (represented as glowing orbs) from a central archive to these doors. Some orbs are historical versions, depicted as slightly faded. Subtle UI elements resembling the Asspp interface are visible on a nearby counter, showing account selection and app search bars. The overall scene is bright and organized, rendered in a clean, 3D isometric illustration style with a vibrant color palette, emphasizing ease of access and organized management of digital applications.
